        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued July 13 at 5:57PM EDT until July 13 at 6:15PM EDT by NWS State College PA</headline>
        <description>At 556 PM EDT, a severe thunderstorm was located over Clearville,
moving northeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

Locations impacted include...
Clearville.

This includes the following Interstates...
Interstate 70 from mile markers 149 to 150.
The Pennsylvania Turnpike from mile markers 159 to 161.
</description>
        <instruction>Stay inside a well built structure and keep away from windows.

Torrential rainfall is occurring with this storm, and may lead to
flash flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways.</instruction>
